org.purewidgets.client.feedback
Interface FeedbackDisplay

All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractInputFeedbackPanel, CumulativeInputFeedbackPanel
public interface FeedbackDisplay

The FeedbackDisplay interface defines the general contract for providing feedback about user input to a specific PdWidget.

Author:
Jorge C. S. Cardoso

setPanelReferencePoint

void setPanelReferencePoint(Align panelReferencePoint)
Sets the reference point of the feedback panel that will be used to position the panel. TOP - Use the top-center point of the panel as a reference.
BOTTOM - Use the bottom-center point of the panel as a reference.
LEFT - Use the left-center point of the panel as a reference.
RIGHT - Use the right-center point of the panel as a reference.
CENTER - Use the center point of the panel as a reference.

Parameters:
panelReferencePoint -

setWidgetReferencePoint

void setWidgetReferencePoint(Align widgetReferencePoint)
Sets the reference point on the PdWidget that will be used to align the the feedback GWT widget. TOP - Use the top-center point of the widget as a reference.
BOTTOM - Use the bottom-center point of the widget as a reference.
LEFT - Use the left-center point of the widget as a reference.
RIGHT - Use the right-center point of the widget as a reference.
CENTER - Use the center point of the widget as a reference.

Parameters:
widgetReferencePoint - The reference point.
